"Comparable replacement dwelling" means any dwelling that is:
Decent, safe, and sanitary;
Adequate in size to accommodate the occupants;
Within the financial means of the displaced person;
Functionally equivalent;
In an area not subject to unreasonable adverse environmental conditions;
In a location generally not less desirable than the location of the displaced person's dwelling with respect to public utilities, facilities, services, and the displaced person's place of employment; and
Currently available on the private market.
